cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.CY 

The paper discusses the durability and fragility of knowledge infrastructures in astronomy, which involves the use of digital archives, metadata, and discovery services. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper draws upon a long-term study of scientific data practices, which involves the use of ethnography and document analysis, suggesting that it may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the different archiving practices between ground- and space-based missions, observational and simulated data, and the coupling of infrastructure components based on international agreements, suggesting that it may belong to the Databases (cs.DB) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-categories.
